Package: twtools
Title:  Utility functions for dealing with tweet data from Twitter
Version: 0.2
Author: Sean Murphy <seanchrismurphy@gmail.com>
Description: twtools is built to accompany the paper "A hands-on guide to using Twitter for psychological research.” It implements several utility functions that make the process of cleaning and using tweet data easier. 
Depends:
    R (>= 3.3.1), rtweet, plyr, dplyr, tidytext, tokenizers, qdap, stringr
License: What license is it under?
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
